Command: TRANSPOSE [/KEEP=varlist] [/DROP=varlist] [/NAME=var$] [/ID=var] [/ARRAY=var]
Reshapes the Data Table so that each transposed column becomes a row.
  /KEEP, /DROP: select which columns to transpose (default: all non-BY
                columns); the effective set is KEEP minus DROP.
  /NAME:  character column that receives the source column name
          in each output row (default: _NAME_$).
  /ID:    column whose values become output column names (wide form);
          mutually exclusive with /ARRAY.
  /ARRAY: base name of the array of transposed values in each output
          row (long form, default: _X_); used when /ID is absent.
Respects the active SELECT filter; transposes each BY block separately.
Flushes a pending SAVE; clears the active SELECT and BY afterward.
Execution: Immediate -- rebuilds the table at once. See man page sdata(1).
